occurrenceRemarks: Closed cerrado vegetation on roadside. Common tree in area reaching c. 10 m when isolated. Spreading canopy from a single trunk. Bark smooth and pale grey. Tree to 2 m, with fruit only. Stem terate, with pricles irregularly positioned along angles os stem. Prickles recurved, shiny with black tip and point away from branch tip. Bark greenish-grey with white lenticles on branches. Young branches have greenish bark with feint ribbing. Leaves with 4-5pairs of pinnae. Leaf rachis with disc-shaped gland at base of petiole. Irregular backward-directed pricles on lower surface of rachis. Rachis of branches covered in short, dense indimentums. One or two fruits per capitate inflorescence, wich is...! Doação do Sistema Herbário UB (6906-0). Goiás
